reviewText: The content of the course is great. The presentation of it is bad, but it is a non-blocking issue for me.HOWEVER!!! I have to stop because of the stupidest peer-graded assessments!So is it my job to monitor when someone submits an assignment????? I am paying money, I am not a millionaire, you know? I want to be done with the courses at the pace I consider is good for me. And the way this course is built is blocking me. It is annoying, frustrating, and makes me very angry!There is no use in the required peer-graded assessments! I am not qualified to grade English grammar! Hello?? I am just a student. Surely I don't care what other people think, unless they are EITHER natives who knows English  well or they are English teachers. I am very VERY frustrated with how you approach the UX of this course. THe only thing I want to do now is to drop it. I've completed EVERYTHING I should have. I want to move forward! And I can't because you just don't care about me as a student.

The Tricky English Grammar course is amazing and very useful for improving your knowledge. However, I could not finish entire these courses in 7 days/free, because reviewing my assignment of the 3rd course took to many days. I have been expecting for 4 days, I had submitted that assignment on 11th April. Unfortunately, I couldn't do this course to end. I am upset with this situation.

The course is actually interesting but this it the only place where I can write down what is in general wrong about the entire course. There is no way to interact with teachers or other students which is causing me a delay in finishing the course. I have finished all my assignment very fast, but I cannot complete the "grade your peers" because there is nothing to grade. Considering that the subscription fee is based on how long you need to finish the course, this is a very unfair system, to make us paying more even if we are actually done. Very disappointed by you.

It is very very bad that only students assess the assignments. Lots of students can't count sentences, can't see and generally are very negligent in evaluating the work of others. No teachers involve the process. No appelation possibility, no forum for discussions!
I really get this courae hard to understand

there are some mistakes in tests
Basic
I think it could be better if can receive the information that explains why I am wrong when I make a mistake in the test, but not just receive a reminder which tells me to look the video again.

There were many things that could be done in a much better way:- The quizzes contain way too less questions. There should be at least 15 to 20 of them to be done in the respect of proving someone's capabilities. These should be drawn by chance out of a much bigger pool - at least three times more than displayed in one quiz. After each trial should be a break of at least one hour to force the student to read and learn about the subject. Now it's enough to memorize the wrong answers and don't mark them again when doing the next trial one minute later. Its way too easy to get a good percentage even if you know pretty nothing.- There are two or sometimes three modules in one week. This is too much. One module - one week. I think the courses should last at least six ( better 8) weeks to assure the topics covered were well understood.- The videos are made in a bad quality - sometimes it sounds as they were recorded by an Edison's phonograph.  - The peer-to-peer assignments should need at least 5 reviews to get an average which is not influenced by a student who has no idea about the topics and is marking correct sentences as wrong ones.- The 'pointage' in the reviews done by peers should offer a wider possibility of differenciation in rating.  - The performance of the orthography should be rated in every review. Nearly a third of the submissions I read were done in a grousy manner.  - The courses 2 and 3 shouldn't run the same course-weeks at the same time. Some students try to save some money and rush through both courses at the same time to get the certificate in less than four weeks. Doing this way, the efficiency decrases. As I already mentioned before, the amount is too much in one week in one course. Redoubling the workload will exacerbate the situation.- The certificates should show the percentage the student earned. It is not very difficult to get a certificate in any of your courses no matter which subject and student's rare knowledge. I earned 100% and get the same certificate as another one who hardly passed. Even there is no credit related to any academical carreer, I'd prefer to impress somebody with a result of A++ written on the certificate.Sincerely, Thomas Zimmermann
